<br>
Well first of all can't use /ooc here. While doing A  /shout 34 druid LFG is acceptable so long as you don't continously spam the zone with it. Keep in mind that many people on the server have shout turned off and for those that don't a more RP shout would go over better such as  &quot;/shout A paladin of the 34th circle looking for companions to help slay these foul orcs&quot;. <br>
<br>
Your best bet to get a group enter the zone you want to hunt in and look around for a group of people hunting If there is less the six wait for a break in the fighting and introduce yourself and ask if you may join. Where this is not possible or highly dangerous, a politely worded tell to people in the zone would work as well.<br>
<br>
Also if not grouped keep your LFG flag on as most of us do check the zone on occasion when we are looking for more party members.<br>
<br>
<br>
Make lots and lots and lots of friends as many zones here are BYOG (bring your own group). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=borblefootfurtoe>borblefoot furtoe</A> at: 1/24/03 4:36:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ifrinnofthebrood>Ifrinn of the brood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/03 5:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2942.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> comment on the TLC</span><hr size=1> A few random thoughts, my apologies if some are repeats. Yes I've been asked all these before in game heh.<br>
<br>
Q: doesn't roleplaying get in the way of, you know, having fun? sounds really dumb to me.<br>
<br>
A: quite the contrary! think of it this way. Would you rather spend hours killing the same mob, hitting the same buttons or hours, then sitting your char and staring at the screen? Or would you rather imagine you've come here to defeat the vile orcs that have been raiding your home lately,or seek one of their teeth to prove to your master how strong you've become?  Or prove how good a bounty hunter you are, collecting their belts to sell for a profit? the possibilities are endless.<br>
<br>
For the Iksar above wanting jboots, I was in the same situation; I went to Ro and 'coerced' a soft skin into killing the cyclops for me. I threatened his life if he didn't slay the cyclops for me, then threw a few coins when he actually survived. Playing Iksar, there's always a rp justification. Throw a bag of platinum at one and he'll happily slaughter other soft skins for you, it's wonderful! and proves how weak and easy to influence they are! You rid the world of a few more miserable soft skins, he gets his coins, everyone wins <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Q: but I really want to raid and be uber!<br>
<br>
A: well good for you. There are 40 odd other servers out there. Yes we have our own high level guilds. But ya know what, they just don't play the same game I do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     They raid, get uber stuff, kill more uberer mobs. I don't get it but hey, they stay out of my happy little rp universe which works fine for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    So however you play, respect the others around you. I've seen what nasty arguments can happen else. <br>
<br>
Q: anything else I should know?<br>
<br>
A: don't announce dings. ever. I mean it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Ya know, if like me you started on this server, the TLC is just.. normal heh. Yes it an be a royal pain sometimes, especially when like me you like to research unsolved quests.. but it still beats no drop hands down in my opinion.<br>
<br>
I play alts on other servers sometimes, and the no drop just baffles me. What, it sticks to my hand?? it was covered in crazy glue? what? eek! It's just never made sense to me. In fact when I come across no drop items, I just... don't know what to do  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
I love this server *smile* <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ifrinnofthebrood>Ifrinn of the brood</A> at: 1/29/03 6:10:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=borblefootfurtoe>borblefoot furtoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 107<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/29/03 11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2942.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Raiding guilds on FV</span><hr size=1> And although we do have several guilds doing high end content here I must say that those guilds are much nicer and are more involved with the community than you would see on a normal blue. As much as we might enjoy griping about them from time to time, they really are much nicer than your average uber guild on other servers.<br>
