<br>
<br>
Well this has been covered here in the FAQ and elsewhere. Basically you have several options. First you can go to where you want to hunt and ask them in say if they want to group. Some places this is not practical so A polite Tell is another way to find out if they are interested in grouping. Thirdly using shout to find a group is also acceptable so long as you are not repeatedly spamming the zone with it. <br>
<br>
Another thing to keep in mind (you don't have to do this if you don't want to, but this is the roleplay server) dress up your grouping requests in roleplay. So instead of shouting level 10 paladin looking for group. You could shout &quot;Paladin 10 seasons young looking to help slay these foul orcs.&quot; or something simlar and appropriate to your character/race roleplay style etc.<br>
<br>
Borblefoot Furtoe<br>
