<br>
I played for about a few days only to discover the fevor that I had so much desired was destroyed by continous innane shouts and OOC's throughout the area. I was dismayed at the extreme lack of roleplaying there and the horrendous amounts of d00d speak. This completely ruined the experience for me and I left, never looking back at the server.<br>
<br>
Occassionally when I log onto EQ, I see FV sitting there at the top of the list, whispering softly to me 'to come back' but I shake my head in dismay as I recall my previous experience there during those saddened days.<br>
<br>
But after coming to this board and reading others posts, a small spark has enticed me to return to the server and give it another try. My mind wracks horribly at the possibility of seeing the innane /shouts and /OOC's flood the chat window. Oh sure I can turn them off, but I am the type who likes to help others when I can, be it with a spell or information that may make their journey easier. My friends call me an <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>official undercover guide</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> because of my level of assisting others... (LOL.. Thanks Natook and Ruusu!) So here's hoping that my next romp through FV will be a sound and just one and that the roleplay experience will once again flow through the land. If you see Shenadraa, feel free to send a greetings!<br>
<br>
Journey well everyone!<br>
